In a non-metallic bowl, combine chicken, lemon juice and salt. Refrigerate 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients for marinade. Pour over chicken and stir until chicken is well coated. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight. Prepare BBQ (medium-high heat) or preheat broiler to high. Thread chicken on bamboo skewers*, about 4 pieces of chicken per kabob. *pre-soak in water for half an hour to prevent burning. Using a pastry brush, brush kabobs with melted BecelÂ® Buttery Taste margarine. Grill or broil until cooked through. Discard any remaining marinade. Serve over a bed of basmati rice.